ts execution ingenious—a masterwork of twentieth-century literary art from an author whom John Updike called “one of the profoundest of the late moderns.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPolish fiction. 0aPolish peoplezArgentinaxHistoryvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBorchardt, Danuta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030017530140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030020701940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300207019423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300207019/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY